Contract Management

Manage and work with data contracts

Contract Parser

Read and decompose data contract files

Arguments
contract_data
Dict[str, Any]
Contract data as dictionary containing schema, metadata, ownership, governance_rules, coercion_rules, and validation_rules
validate(optional)
booldefault: True
If True (default), validate contract against schema before parsing
Returns
ContractMetadata
ContractMetadata object with decomposed components (schema, metadata, ownership, governance_rules, coercion_rules, validation_rules) and version tracking
from pycharter import parse_contract, parse_contract_file

parse_contract(contract_dict)
parse_contract_file(file_path)
Method: parse_contract(contract_dict, validate=True)
Test API
POST /api/v1/contracts/parse

Contract Parser - From File

Parse a data contract from an uploaded file (YAML or JSON)

Arguments
file_path
str
Path to contract file (YAML or JSON)
validate(optional)
booldefault: True
If True (default), validate contract against schema before parsing
Returns
ContractMetadata
ContractMetadata object with decomposed components (schema, metadata, ownership, governance_rules, coercion_rules, validation_rules)
from pycharter import parse_contract_file

# Parse contract from file
contract_metadata = parse_contract_file("contract.yaml")
# or
contract_metadata = parse_contract_file("contract.json", validate=True)
Method: parse_contract_file(file_path, validate=True)
Test API
POST /api/v1/contracts/parse/upload

Contract Builder

Construct consolidated contracts from separate artifacts

Arguments
artifacts
ContractArtifacts
ContractArtifacts dataclass containing schema (required), coercion_rules (optional), validation_rules (optional), and metadata (optional)
include_metadata(optional)
booldefault: True
Whether to include metadata in the contract
include_ownership(optional)
booldefault: True
Whether to include ownership information
include_governance(optional)
booldefault: True
Whether to include governance rules
Returns
Dict[str, Any]
Consolidated contract dictionary ready for runtime validation, containing schema (with merged coercion/validation rules), coercion_rules, validation_rules, metadata (if included), and versions tracking dictionary
from pycharter import build_contract, ContractArtifacts

artifacts = ContractArtifacts(
    schema={"type": "object", "version": "1.0.0", "properties": {...}},
    coercion_rules={"version": "1.0.0", "age": "coerce_to_integer"},
    validation_rules={"version": "1.0.0", "age": {...}},
    metadata={"version": "1.0.0", "description": "User contract"}
)
contract = build_contract(artifacts)
Method: build_contract(artifacts: ContractArtifacts, include_metadata=True, include_ownership=True, include_governance=True)
Test API
POST /api/v1/contracts/build

Contract Builder - From Store

Build a consolidated contract from artifacts stored in metadata store with individual version control for each component

Arguments
store
MetadataStoreClient
MetadataStoreClient instance connected to the metadata store
schema_title
str
Schema title/identifier
schema_version(optional)
Optional[str]default: None
Optional schema version (if None, uses latest version)
coercion_rules_title(optional)
Optional[str]default: None
Optional coercion rules title/identifier (if None, uses schema_title)
coercion_rules_version(optional)
Optional[str]default: None
Optional coercion rules version (if None, uses latest version or schema_version)
validation_rules_title(optional)
Optional[str]default: None
Optional validation rules title/identifier (if None, uses schema_title)
validation_rules_version(optional)
Optional[str]default: None
Optional validation rules version (if None, uses latest version or schema_version)
metadata_title(optional)
Optional[str]default: None
Optional metadata title/identifier (if None, uses schema_title)
metadata_version(optional)
Optional[str]default: None
Optional metadata version (if None, uses latest version or schema_version)
Returns
Dict[str, Any]
Consolidated contract dictionary ready for runtime validation, containing schema (with merged coercion/validation rules), coercion_rules, validation_rules, metadata (if included), and versions tracking dictionary
from pycharter import build_contract_from_store

store = PostgresMetadataStore(connection_string)
store.connect()
contract = build_contract_from_store(
    store=store,
    schema_title="user_schema",
    schema_version="1.0.0",
    coercion_rules_title="user_schema",
    coercion_rules_version="1.0.0",
    validation_rules_title="user_schema",
    validation_rules_version="1.0.0",
    metadata_title="user_schema",
    metadata_version="1.0.0"
)
Method: build_contract_from_store(store, schema_title, schema_version=None, coercion_rules_title=None, coercion_rules_version=None, validation_rules_title=None, validation_rules_version=None, metadata_title=None, metadata_version=None)
Test API
POST /api/v1/contracts/build
